java.io.Serializable
public class LocationMismatchException
extends java.lang.Exception

Author:
jaschasilbermann A Location Mismatch Exception is thrown when attempts are made to mix information coming from different Genomic Locations. For example, trying to construct a Complex Sequence from two Simple Sequences from different Genomic Locations will result in a Location Mismatch Exception being thrown.
